      </li>
    </startSignals>
    <promptEnabled>false</promptEnabled>
    <promptWeight>0</promptWeight>
  </PawnDiary.DiaryEventWindowDef>

  <PawnDiary.DiaryEventWindowDef>
    <defName>VeeStampede</defName>
    <label>VEE mass animal attack</label>
    <windowKey>VeeStampede</windowKey>
    <enabled>true</enabled>
    <enableWhenPackageIdsLoaded>
      <li>VanillaExpanded.VEE</li>
    </enableWhenPackageIdsLoaded>
    <timeoutTicks>-1</timeoutTicks>
    <dedupTicks>2500</dedupTicks>
    <restartOnStart>false</restartOnStart>
    <keepActive>false</keepActive>
    <recordScope>MapWitness</recordScope>
    <recordStartEvent>true</recordStartEvent>
    <recordEndEvent>false</recordEndEvent>
    <recordEndWithoutActive>false</recordEndWithoutActive>
    <recordTimeoutEvent>false</recordTimeoutEvent>
    <instruction>write animals gone wrong at impossible scale; focus on the approaching mass, noise, and panic without inventing how the fight ends</instruction>
    <colorCue>danger</colorCue>
    <startTextKey>PawnDiary.Event.EventWindow.VeeStampede.Start</startTextKey>
    <startSignals>
      <li>
        <source>Incident</source>
        <signal>executed</signal>
        <matchDefNames>
          <li>ManhunterPackPurple</li>
          <li>AnimalInsanityMassPurple</li>
        </matchDefNames>
      </li>
    </startSignals>
    <promptEnabled>false</promptEnabled>
    <promptWeight>0</promptWeight>
  </PawnDiary.DiaryEventWindowDef>

  <!-- Display groups: orders 145-147 are intentionally between the existing event groups
       (137-144) and the Interaction catch-all (150). Disjoint exact names make sharing order 145
       deterministic and harmless. -->
  <PawnDiary.DiaryInteractionGroupDef>
    <defName>eventWindowVeeEarthquake</defName>
    <label>Earthquake</label>
    <order>145</order>
    <domain>Interaction</domain>
    <defaultEnabled>true</defaultEnabled>
    <important>true</important>
    <colorCue>danger</colorCue>
    <enableWhenPackageIdsLoaded>
      <li>VanillaExpanded.VEE</li>
    </enableWhenPackageIdsLoaded>
    <instruction>the ground itself turning traitor; write the shaking and the first honest damage count, never an invented outcome</instruction>
    <instructions>
      <li>an earthquake — open on balance, sound, dust, or something fixed beginning to move</li>
      <li>an earthquake — write the first still moment afterward and only the damage the pawn can actually see</li>
    </instructions>
    <tone>with helpless, ground-deep alarm</tone>
    <tones>
      <li>shaken and physical, the floor no longer trustworthy</li>
      <li>stunned and practical, counting what still stands</li>
    </tones>
    <matchDefNames>
      <li>VEE_Earthquake</li>
    </matchDefNames>
  </PawnDiary.DiaryInteractionGroupDef>

  <PawnDiary.DiaryInteractionGroupDef>
    <defName>eventWindowVeeMeteoriteShower</defName>
    <label>Meteorite shower</label>
    <order>145</order>
    <domain>Interaction</domain>
    <defaultEnabled>true</defaultEnabled>
    <important>true</important>
    <colorCue>danger</colorCue>
    <enableWhenPackageIdsLoaded>
      <li>VanillaExpanded.VEE</li>
    </enableWhenPackageIdsLoaded>
    <instruction>fire from the sky with awe and danger mixed; write the first impacts without inventing where every stone lands</instruction>
    <instructions>
      <li>a meteorite shower — write light, sound, and the terrible beauty of the first descent</li>
      <li>a meteorite shower — keep awe beside practical fear: shelter, fire, and exposed ground, only as supplied</li>
    </instructions>
    <tone>with sky-struck awe under immediate danger</tone>
    <tones>
      <li>awed and frightened, unable to look away</li>
      <li>bright, violent, and alert to every impact</li>
    </tones>
    <matchDefNames>
      <li>VEE_MeteoriteShower</li>
    </matchDefNames>
  </PawnDiary.DiaryInteractionGroupDef>

  <PawnDiary.DiaryInteractionGroupDef>
    <defName>eventWindowVeeSpaceBattle</defName>
    <label>Orbital disaster</label>
    <order>146</order>
    <domain>Interaction</domain>
    <defaultEnabled>true</defaultEnabled>
    <important>true</important>
    <colorCue>danger</colorCue>
    <enableWhenPackageIdsLoaded>
      <li>VanillaExpanded.VEE</li>
    </enableWhenPackageIdsLoaded>
    <instruction>a battle or wreck overhead that has nothing and everything to do with the colony; write what falls into their lives, not an invented war story</instruction>
    <instructions>
      <li>an orbital disaster — keep the distant war unknowable and the falling wreckage immediate</li>
      <li>an orbital disaster — write the scale above and the smallness of the colony beneath it, using only supplied facts</li>
    </instructions>
    <tone>with distant-war awe and close practical fear</tone>
    <tones>
      <li>small beneath an enormous, indifferent conflict</li>
      <li>watchful and stunned, the sky spilling someone else's disaster</li>
    </tones>
    <matchDefNames>
      <li>VEE_SpaceBattle</li>
      <li>VEE_ShuttleCrash</li>
    </matchDefNames>
  </PawnDiary.DiaryInteractionGroupDef>

  <PawnDiary.DiaryInteractionGroupDef>
    <defName>eventWindowVeeStampede</defName>
    <label>Mass animal attack</label>
    <order>147</order>
    <domain>Interaction</domain>
    <defaultEnabled>true</defaultEnabled>
    <important>true</important>
    <combat>true</combat>
    <colorCue>danger</colorCue>
    <enableWhenPackageIdsLoaded>
      <li>VanillaExpanded.VEE</li>
    </enableWhenPackageIdsLoaded>
    <instruction>animals gone wrong at impossible scale; write the mass, noise, and panic at first approach, never an invented victory</instruction>
    <instructions>
      <li>a mass animal attack — open on too many bodies moving as one and the sound reaching the colony</li>
      <li>a mass animal attack — write the defense becoming arithmetic: doors, fields, ammunition, and nowhere enough time</li>
    </instructions>
    <tone>with stampeding, numberless panic</tone>
    <tones>
      <li>overwhelmed by scale, danger arriving on too many feet</li>
      <li>fast and defensive, panic forced into practical choices</li>
    </tones>
    <matchDefNames>
      <li>ManhunterPackPurple</li>
      <li>AnimalInsanityMassPurple</li>
    </matchDefNames>
  </PawnDiary.DiaryInteractionGroupDef>

